If it’s the same header you use across the site, I would just add the button to the header and add a check to see if the user is logged in.

```{% if request_contact.is_logged_in %}
    //show sign-out button
{% else %}
    //do whatever
{% endif %}```
Otherwise, you’d want to create a new layout template that uses a different header, but you’d still put the same check as above.

Edit to get around edge cases where the user is signed in, you are using the same global header across the site, and you DON'T want the button to show regardless - You'd just create a template level field for something like "show_auth_buttons"
